From 651f14bb7f58f9c1ce2762a9f2c68f08680d4bd1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 16:55:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Mutation error handling: fix silent failures in 6 handlers
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Outside-audit cleanup. Adds try/catch + user-visible toast to six
handleSave/handleAction handlers that called base44.entities.X.update/
create without error handling. On failure, the user would see a stuck
loading spinner with no feedback; the operation had to be diagnosed
from the Network tab.

Scope re-evaluation during reconnaissance:

  Originally planned as 'mutation toast consolidation' — migrate sites
  to useMutation, centralize toast in mutationCache.onError. But grep
  showed ZERO sites currently use useMutation (the mutationCache.onError
  comment is aspirational). That migration is a 2-4 hour refactor, too
  big for a finisher PR.

  Instead: real bug fix with the same 30-60 min budget. 5 of 6 handlers
  had no error handling at all — silent failure on any mutation error
  (network, validation, permission). AdminDashboard.handleAction is
  the worst offender: if MemberApplication.update or User.update fails,
  processing state never resets and the approve/reject button hangs
  forever.

Sites fixed (all wrap the mutation in try/catch, toast on failure,
restore loading state, early-return from the success path):

  1. src/pages/dashboard/AdminDashboard.jsx — handleAction
     Was: two member updates without try/catch, then email in its own
     try/catch with an empty catch.
     Now: member updates are the critical path (try/catch + toast +
     reset), email stays best-effort (try/catch + log only, so an
     email failure doesn't block a successful approval).

  2. src/pages/admin/Members.jsx — handleSave
     Single User.update; try/catch + toast + setSaving(false).

  3. src/pages/TCProfilePage.jsx — handleSave
     TCProfile.update or .create; try/catch + toast + setSaving(false).

  4. src/pages/InvestorProfilePage.jsx — handleSave
     Same pattern as TC.

  5. src/pages/PMLProfilePage.jsx — handleSave
     Same pattern as TC.

  6. src/components/deals/PostDealForm.jsx — handleSubmit
     Deal.update or .create; try/catch + toast + setSaving(false).
     On error, dialog stays open so the user can retry.

New file: src/lib/toasts.js

  Single helper (toastMutationError(action)) that wraps toast.error
  with the 'Failed to ${action}. Please try again.' phrasing. Matches
  the existing inline 'Failed to X. Please try again.' style used
  in ~13 other handlers, so new error toasts blend in with the old.

  This file is also the natural home for future toast utilities. If a
  later PR migrates handlers to useMutation, mutationCache.onError in
  query-client.js can call toastMutationError to centralize the toast
  without changing copy.

Not in scope (follow-ups):

  - Existing 'Failed to X' toasts NOT migrated to the helper. They
    work fine; migrating them would touch ~10 more files for zero
    user-visible change. The helper is available when someone wants
    to do that cleanup.

  - useMutation migration. Would be the 'right' architecture per the
    query-client.js comment, but it's multi-hour work touching ~10
    handlers. This PR delivers the real bug fix (visible errors)
    without the architecture change.

  - DealBoard, Messages, PartnersPage, DealDetailModal all already
    have try/catch with user feedback (inline setError or toast);
    untouched.

Verification:

  - npm run lint: 0 errors (full codebase)
  - Scoped lint: 0 errors, 3 pre-existing warnings
  - npm run build: succeeds
  - All new catch handlers log to console.error AND show toast, so
    debugging info isn't lost when the user-facing toast fires

